main event: A disc shaped, pinkish-orange object was observed over Keflavik Airport on October 8, 1952, by four officers of 932 ACW Sq.
interesting points: The object traveled at high speed, 2-3,000 feet, and hovered momentarily over the airport., The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes., The object disappeared with no cloud cover in sight., Numerous stars and planets were visible, but the objects did not appear to be blinking lights., The radar at Keflavik installation did not pick up any targets corresponding to the objects.
